overview: The user wanted to add a database and an admin dashboard to their
  Sleep Questionnaire Application. The agent evaluated the existing codebase,
  identified missing components, and created a plan. Key implementations
  included a Prisma schema for questionnaire responses, API endpoints for data
  handling (save, list, CSV export), and an admin dashboard with a login page.
  Initially, a custom session-based authentication system was built, but upon
  user query, it was simplified to leverage Next.js middleware for more
  efficient route protection. The agent provided detailed instructions for
  database setup using NeonDB and environment variables. During the testing
  phase, it was discovered that the 'Pre-fill & Jump to Report' button did not
  trigger the database submission, which the agent identified as needing a
  proper form submission for data to be saved.
